predict_diagnosis:
1. Fibromyomatosis uterinae (uterine leiomyoma)
2. Cardiomyopathy, dilated
3. Valvular heart disease (abnormal tricuspid valve morphology)
4. Right ventricular dysfunction
5. Hypertrophic cardiomyopathy
6. Pulmonary hypertension
7. Arrhythmia (paroxysmal ventricular tachycardia, paroxysmal atrial tachycardia, premature ventricular contraction)
8. Heart failure (right and left ventricular dysfunction, increased NT-proBNP)
9. Systemic disease (weight loss, poor appetite, nausea, exertional dyspnea)
10. Infectious etiology (nonproductive cough)

Please note that this list is not exhaustive, and the actual diagnosis should be determined by a healthcare professional after thorough evaluation and diagnostic testing.
